  <sys:String x:Key="MarkChallengeCompleteButton">✓ Mark Challenge Complete (Pattern B v1)</sys:String>
  <sys:String x:Key="MarkChallengeCompleteTip">Engine-faithful single-challenge completion (Pattern B v1). Only enables when the game has already detected this challenge as available (you've picked up the sealed artifact in-game). Writes the relevant entries — exactly what the game itself writes for a completed-but-unclaimed state. Living-type challenges may not apply. NOT FULLY TESTED — back up your save first.</sys:String>
  <sys:String x:Key="MarkChallengeSkipReasonPrefix">Disabled — reason:</sys:String>

  <!-- Structural-edit (length-changing) save warning. Shown before a Save
       when the pending edits change the body length. -->
  <sys:String x:Key="StructuralEditWarningTitle">Structural edit — may not load</sys:String>
  <sys:String x:Key="StructuralEditWarningBody" xml:space="preserve">This save has length-changing (structural) edits, such as completing a sealed abyss artifact challenge or adding/removing list items.&#10;&#10;The data is written correctly, but Crimson Desert's own save loader has a bug that can make some heavily-progressed saves crash on load after such an edit. In-place edits (item counts, states, gate/flag toggles) are safe.&#10;&#10;A backup of the original is kept. Save anyway?</sys:String>

  <!-- Sealed-artifact "Mark Challenge Complete" confirm dialog. Detail is a
       format string: {0}=challenge key, {1}=internal name, {2}=twin key,
       {3}=FAR idx, {4}=FAR key, {5}=update/create word, {6}=follow-up key,
       {7}=follow-up internal name, {8}=tags before, {9}=tags after,
       {10}=the follow-up bullet line (already newline-terminated). -->
  <sys:String x:Key="MarkChallengeConfirmTitle">Mark challenge complete (Pattern B v1)?</sys:String>
  <sys:String x:Key="MarkChallengeWordUpdate">update</sys:String>
  <sys:String x:Key="MarkChallengeWordCreate">create</sys:String>
  <sys:String x:Key="MarkChallengeFollowUpExists" xml:space="preserve">  • X_2 sub-mission entry already exists; skipped insert.&#10;</sys:String>
  <sys:String x:Key="MarkChallengeFollowUpNew" xml:space="preserve">  • NEW MissionStateData entry appended (cloned from FAR tracker, _key + _branchedTime patched to the X_2 sub-mission shape).&#10;</sys:String>
  <sys:String x:Key="MarkChallengeConfirmDetail" xml:space="preserve">Mark this challenge as completed using the Pattern B v1 recipe?&#10;&#10;  Challenge key: {0}&#10;  Internal name: {1}&#10;  Adjacent visibility twin key: {2}&#10;  FAR tracker: idx {3}, key {4}&#10;  X_2 sub-mission to {5}: key {6} ({7})&#10;&#10;What this writes:&#10;  • FAR tracker _state ← 5 + _completedTime stamped.&#10;  • FAR tracker _usedTagList: {8} → {9} entries (adds visible magic tag).&#10;{10}  • Catalog row + adjacent twin: UNTOUCHED. Engine handles those at reward pickup.&#10;&#10;</sys:String>
  <sys:String x:Key="MarkChallengeConfirmWarnings" xml:space="preserve">[!! HOLD THE MATCHING ARTIFACT] Confirm that the Sealed Abyss Artifact for THIS specific challenge is currently in your inventory. The button only enables when you hold at least one SA artifact (any variant), but the in-game reward-claim flow on next reload only completes if the matching artifact for this challenge is in your bag. Pattern B v1 on its own is not enough — the artifact pickup is the engine's gating signal.&#10;&#10;[!! VERIFIED ON Shield II / Spear I / Hooves II / Slash III IN SLOT102] Pattern B v1 is reverse-engineered from the engine's natural Hooves II completion (slot102 → live slot103 transition). The recipe writes the pre-claim state and lets the engine finish bookkeeping on next load. Earlier patterns that tried to write the post-claim state directly all corrupted the in-game UI. CONFIRM YOUR SAVE IS BACKED UP before proceeding (auto-backup at %LOCALAPPDATA%\CrimsonAtomtic\Backups\ — File → Restore from Backup… can roll back).&#10;&#10;[!! WILL AFFECT GAME PROGRESSION] Forcing the FAR tracker to state=5 tells the engine the challenge is complete; downstream content / NPC dialogues that depend on this challenge being done will trigger.&#10;&#10;[!! ACHIEVEMENTS WILL NOT UNLOCK] Steam / platform achievements only fire on a real in-game completion. Marking via file edit will not trigger the achievement, and once the challenge is in this state the engine won't re-fire it on subsequent legitimate completion. Do not use this for challenges you intend to complete legitimately later.&#10;&#10;Proceed?</sys:String>
  <sys:String x:Key="MarkChallengeCancelled">Mark cancelled.</sys:String>

  <sys:String x:Key="ConfirmDialogYes">Yes</sys:String>
  <sys:String x:Key="ConfirmDialogNo">No</sys:String>
